Name: Bonus Morale
Description: More morale is always preferable. These troops are less likely to flee or surrender in a losing fight.

Name: Heroic
Description: Heroes do not fear failure or death, but that does not mean they welcome it.

Name: Varied Training
Description: The lack of standardised training makes the troops' fighting ability wildly diverse.

Name: Zealous
Description: Being zealous for one's belief can make soldiers less susceptible to fear.

Name: Poor Morale
Description: Either from poor training or by its nature, these soldiers have poorer morale making them unfit for prolonged or serious engagements.

Name: Tough Painting
Description: Orc Berserkers usually wear no armour at all and paint their naked body into battle. What is little known is that the paint materials used are so tough when they are hardened that they can actually stop a sword or arrow.

Name: Impregnable Shield
Description: One of the most basic equipment to keep one alive in a chaotic battle. Having one is almost always better than having none but having one that is of superb quality is the best of all.

Name: Protective Fur
Description: Some beastmen or creatures have furs thick enough to protect against some attack to a degree. Additionally, it can help against cold too.

Name: Charge Expert
Description: A charge is one of the most powerful tactics in battles in the past that can decide the battle. Being well-versed in charging is never a disadvantage.

Name: Charge Defense Expert
Description: Why settle for just defending when you can turn the enemies' charge into their own demise.

Name: Weapon Expert
Description: Decades of perfection the weapon make these soldiers a pinnacle of all warriors.

Name: Evasive
Description: These troops can dodge melee and range attacks when fighting in loose formation.

Name: Arc Shot
Description: Arc shot allows archers to shoot past the obstacle to hit the target they aiming for. *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Agile Aims
Description: These troops can shoot while moving and at moving enemy without penalty. A feat only the greatest archer can achieve. This property also helps improve accuracy against moving targets.

Name: Can Shoot While Moving
Description: These troops can shoot while moving but with some accuracy penalty. Requires a lot of archery training, but the result is undoubtedly beneficial.

Name: Concentrated Aims
Description: The accuracy of these troops are not affected by morale (they still cannot shoot when in a broken state).

Name: Concentrated Chant
Description: These troops’ magic casting is not affected by morale (they still cannot cast magic when in a broken state).

Name: Anti-Infantry
Description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy infantries *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Anti-Flyer
Description: What goes up must come down. These troops are specialised in combat against flyer enemies.

Name: Anti-Cavalry
Description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy cavalries. Bring an end to the age of cavalry one step at a time. *This trait can be obtained from certain weapons.

Name: Anti-Mage
Description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy mages. Not even the wisest wizards can survive this hunt.

Name: Anti-Machine
Description: These troops are specialised in combat against enemy machines. Neither Iron nor wood can not stop their attacks.

Name: Anti-Large
Description: The bigger they are, the harder they fall. These troops are specialised in combat against large enemies.

Name: Anti-All
Description: The destroyer of the world. No man, beast, nor machine can withstand this true might.

Name: Anti-Structure
Description: Tear down the wall! No structure can withstand such strong force.

Name: Ignore Charge Defense
Description: A rush of death and ruin. The world shall tremble upon this sight. These troops’ charge ignores charge defence entirely.

Name: Ignore Defense
Description: Deadly to those unfortunate to face them in combat. These troops’ attacks ignore defence entirely.

Name: Cannibal
Description: Taboo most foul. But one death can sustain another life.

Name: Defiant Defense
Description: Only the strongest force can take down these troops. They will struggle to the end, and for every one man killed, they will take down 10 enemies with them.

Name: Backstaber
Description: These troops deal bonus damage to enemies with rear attacks.

Name: Battle Master
Description: These troops can fully attack enemies in all directions and suffer no defence penalty from being flanked.

Name: Absolute Defense
Description: The best defence is a good offence. It may be important to kill the enemy to win the battle, but it is more important to survive to win a war.

Name: Great Saint
Description: The best of the best in the realm. These troops help nearby allies to be at maximum morale and cannot be decreased.

Name: Battle Saint
Description: Greatest in battle and greatest in combat. These saintly troops will surely lead their allies to victory.

Name: No Hunger
Description: These troops cannot get hungry, which means they do not need a food supply to maintain at all.

Name: Patriotic
Description: It is the duty of every citizen to fight for the country they live in. These troops fight much better in friendly territory and require less upkeep.

Name: Siege Expert
Description: No wall is safe from these soldiers! They can fight much better in siege combat. All defense +15% during siege, siege progression speed +50%.

Name: Unadvancable
Description: These troops cannot gain experience from normal means.

Name: Hunger Instinct
Description: Hunger is one of the most important factors for aggressivity in most animals. If these troops are in the hunger stage, they will fight much harder than usual to obtain foods, which in this case is the enemy in front of them.

Name: Famed
Description: These troops have been fighting through many battles and wars, gaining them the fame they deserve. Increase some morale for allies nearby while reducing for enemies.

Name: Shield Expert
Description: Survive to fight another day by improving your defence is never a bad idea.

Name: Crumble
Description: Nothing last forever, even for inanimate material creatures. Time has rendered these troops much less powerful compared to their former glory.

Name: Superb Flanker
Description: These troops fight better against enemies from flanking positions.

Name: Bandit Honour
Description: The way of bandit usually is not appropriate to the code of honour. It must be extremely difficult and remarkable for one to uphold whatever honour vow they swear to.

Name: True Hero
Description: Being true heroes, these troops have a manifestly inspiring aura for nearby allies.

Name: Legendary Might
Description: The might of the legends cannot be subdued. Beware the enemy for the death to come.

Name: Magical Weapon
Description: These troops’ weapons have magic property, which deals additional magic damage and can deal damage to Incorporeal enemies.

Name: Oblivious To Unexpected
Description: These soldiers are so oblivious to unexpected events that they have no idea or plan to defend against them, making them receive a defence penalty from rear attacks.

Name: Causes Fear
Description: Only the brave can resist fear, and those are the ones that die young.

Name: Causes Terror
Description: Terror is in the mind until it manifests into reality in front of you. Fleeing is always an option.

Name: Inspires Hope
Description: Instilling hope in your brother in arms is one of the greatest achievements one can perform in an army.

Name: Inspires Bravery
Description: Bravery is a rare luxury in a place like a battlefield. To share such rarity with others is a noble deed indeed.

Name: Hope And Despair
Description: A bringer of hope yet also a herald of calamity. Can it be the result of insanity?

Name: Glorious Appearance
Description: These troops’ appearances are so dashing and inspiring that nearby allies will be in awe while leaving enemies in fear.

Name: Holy Defense
Description: The blood and sins of the devil can veil one's mind. The lost sheep will then follow the true teaching.

Name: Vile Veil
Description: There are none without sin and their sins will make them blind.

Name: Xenophobic Bunch
Description: These troops loathe fighting together with soldiers or creatures from other races than themselves.

Name: Eyes Of Satiens
Description: Discern the path, exact the truth. These troops suffer no range penalty and can shoot even further than usual.

Name: Farsight
Description: Farsight reduces accuracy penalty from long-range shooting and also make these troops see enemies’ projectiles earlier.

Name: No Range Penalty
Description: Assured accuracy to eradicate the enemy from any location.

Name: Long Range Accuracy
Description: Death from afar, the end of the chivalric era is near.

Name: Entertainer
Description: Entertainment may look like it has no place in this hell. But it sure improves the soldiers’ morale.

Name: Missile Resistance
Description: Piecing damage from missiles can do little damage to these troops. Not even a hail of arrows can stop their advance.

Name: Pain Resistance
Description: Ultimate soldiers. Pain and suffering is not even a concept to these monsters of war.

Name: Poison Resistance
Description: Underhand tactics will not work well on these troops. Try crushing them with raw might instead.

Name: Cold Resistance
Description: Cold resistance allows these troops to resist the negative effect of cold terrain and weather.

Name: Heat Resistance
Description: Heat resistance allows these troops to resist the negative effect of hot terrain and weather.

Name: Fatigue Resistance
Description: Fatigue is the natural consequence of any physical activity. It just comes much later for some than the others.

Name: Magic Resistance
Description: Unscientific matters are of minor concern for these troops. All mages loath them for their antithesis.

Name: Swamp Crosser
Description: Bonus to combat and movement for these troops in swamp terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Sylvan
Description: Bonus to combat and movement for these troops in forest terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Blight Habitat
Description: Bonus to combat and movement for these troops in blight terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Aquatic
Description: Bonus to combat and movement for these troops in water terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: Urban Guerrilla
Description: Bonus to combat and movement for these troops in urban terrain and also use less supply as well.

Name: First Blood
Description: These troops will deal bonus damage to enemies if they and the enemies both have no injury or death.

Name: Fervent Devotion
Description: These troops fight better when being near their commander.

Name: No Morale
Description: These troops have no morale thus can not be motivated or broken.

Name: Knightly Valour
Description: The valour of a knight is often a sight to behold for both enemy and friend. Often time, the flow of battle can change completely just from these knights’ presence.

Name: Thorny Armour
Description: Enemies that attack these troops in melee combat will also receive damage in return.

Name: Unstoppable
Description: Unstoppable force. Stand aside or perish.

Name: Battle Preparation
Description: These troops receive a combat bonus when their stamina is at a fresh level.

Name: Blessed
Description: To the blessed heaven shall assist. The world is blight and the sky is clear.

Name: Cursed
Description: A cursed being either by means of magic or nature, these troops will always be cursed and cannot be cured by normal means.

Name: Lucky
Description: With luck on their side, surely no one can deny their destiny.

Name: Unlucky
Description: Born under the wrong star or maybe some witches hold grudges against them, these troops usually fail at every task more than succeed.

Name: Fanatical Backstabbing
Description: "Of course, it's personal because it's fun!", Midjilipun, the Big Boss of the Ritdukub clan in an exclusive interview with Chavu of Dina. Goblins really take joy in the art of backstabbing each other. Some can say it is a game or even a part of their nature for them.

Name: Tireless
Description: Absolute killing machine! These troops' fatigue cannot be decreased, making their combat effectiveness stay at the best condition for the whole fight.

Name: Unbreakable
Description: Fleeing or surrendering is never an option for those with true honour and bravery. Death is a better option than dishonour.

Name: Savage Looter
Description: These troops know well how to steal and plunder. While neither honourable nor noble, gold is essential even when running an army.

Name: Catcher Expert
Description: A good enemy is not always a dead enemy. Prisoner of war often brings good ransom money, especially when it comes to captive noble.

Name: Marvelous Athletic
Description: These troops being athletic superior makes them much more effective in long activities such as fighting.

Name: Iron Discipline
Description: These troops receive further bonus effects from discipline.

Name: Curse Strike
Description: Attacks imbued with hatred. Blood will not stop flowing and vigour will keep draining.

Name: Infective Touch
Description: Who can blame the unfortunates that want to spread misfortune to the others? The world is too bright for fake happiness.

Name: Mana Stealer
Description: Every strike from these troops will sap away the mana of any enemy mage. Manaless mages make for nothing but useless pieces of baggage.

Name: Battlelust
Description: Nothing is better than soldiers who are thirsty for battle. They are the ones that always fight the hardest.

Name: Headtaker
Description: These troops often decapitate enemy heads in combat as tokens. This will decrease their combat effectiveness by a bit but reduce enemy morale from damage further.

Name: Nasty Smell
Description: These troops have a disgusting stench that makes anyone that not familiar with it want to throw up. Every nearby enemy receives a combat penalty.

Name: Poison Blood
Description: Completely immune to poison and dangerous to enemies when attacked. The ultimate evolution trait for revenge.

Name: Mirage Trickery
Description: Not even the most accurate archer in the realm can shoot at a mirage, for the mind and reality are not the same.

Name: Martial Perfection
Description: The life of devotion to martial perfection is not uncommon in times of chaos. But rare still to see those who have perfected it.

Name: Forgetful
Description: Forget order sometimes.

Name: Joyful Departure
Description: Stemming from their peculiar tradition, these troops gain more morale when nearby ally troops are destroyed.

Name: High Jumper
Description: These troops can jump quite high when attacking, making them negate the height penalty from critical by one level.

Name: Unkillable
Description: These troops cannot be killed by normal means.

Name: Lone Wolf
Description: Rather fighting alone on the battlefield. The fewer friendly allies nearby, the more effective these troops become.

Name: Rotten Smell
Description: Inducing vomit odour can cause great mental effects to the unfortunate victims.

Name: Wall Climbing
Description: These troops can bypass walls easily. They do not require siege equipment in order to go above any wall but may suffer damage if the wall is filled with an anti-climbing trap and do not receive any defence bonus from siege equipment.

Name: Hero Killer
Description: These troops deal more damage to champion and hero grade enemies.

Name: Command Independent
Description: These troops’ morale will not be affected by the commander's death or retreat.

Name: Impetuous
Description: Whether from pride or arrogance, these troops have a tendency to follow orders even less when the leader makes a mistake or issue a command they do not like.

Name: Hearty Competition
Description: Being the elite of the elite, these elite troops see battles as a game of who kills the most enemy. The more they kill, the higher their morale, including nearby allies.

Name: Battle Juggernaut
Description: Unflinching to most strike. These troops are so formidable that it will take more than a simple tactic to eliminate them.

Name: Heroic Spirit
Description: These troops are being led by a heroic spirit from the past. This makes the troops in high spirit when following their great hero into battle.

Name: Deathwish
Description: These troops fight like it seeks death itself. Their morale can never be decreased.

Name: Troll Blood
Description: Troll blood helps its body heal any wound it receives much faster than other creatures, even during combat.

Name: Hope Crusher
Description: When there is despair, there is hope. And it is the duty of these troops to crush whatever tiny hope the enemies still have left.

Name: Merciless
Description: These troops cannot capture running enemies as they always prefer killing them instead.

Name: Fragile Will
Description: These troops will be affected by negative psychological effects even more than usual.

Name: Overwhelming Presence
Description: These creatures’ appearance is so overwhelming that they leave both friendly and enemy troops in fear and worry.

Name: Headshotter
Description: Precise. It is best to aim for a certain kill when you are able.

Name: Perfect Aims
Description: Never a shot wasted when the enemies are lining up to be killed.

Name: Personal Escort
Description: Trained to escort important people to safety, these troops will allow any leader they protect to survive for much longer in a chaotic battle.

Name: Domination Aura
Description: When enemies become broken near these creatures, they will join these troops' sides instead of freeing.

Name: Fire Being
Description: Fire damage actually heals these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Water Being
Description: Water damage actually heals these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Air Being
Description: Air damage actually heals these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Earth Being
Description: Earth damage actually heals these creatures instead of damaging them.

Name: Icy Being
Description: Being made of ice, these creatures receive healing instead of damage from frozen status.

Name: Shadow Fog
Description: Their shadow being creates a fog that makes it impossible to clearly observe the area nearby.

Name: Penetration Shots
Description: These troops’ range attacks are so powerful that they can penetrate enemy bodies and damage more than one enemy per shot. They can also shoot through a weak obstacle and deals minor damage to a major obstacle.

Name: Unholy Flesh
Description: These troops can not be healed and will instead receive damage from healing magic.

Name: Field Medic
Description: These troops can heal nearby allies when both are not in melee combat.

Name: Divine Presence
Description: These troops are divine or considered to be divine by their followers. They will make every ally on the battlefield at maximum morale and cannot be broken.

Name: Plague Carrier
Description: Undeniably unethical in the rule of warfare. Fight dirty to bring the suffering that continues until the end of your enemy's life.

Name: Blight Bearer
Description: Enemy of all lives. The blight will spread and consume. And now will survive.

Name: Forestry
Description: No penalty in forest terrain for these troops.

Name: Seamate
Description: Ahoy matey! Less movement and combat penalty on sea terrain for these troops.

Name: Mountaineer
Description: Less movement and combat penalty from mountain terrain for these troops.

Name: Cave Crawling
Description: Less movement and combat penalty in underground terrain for these troops.

Name: Pathfinder
Description: Half Movement penalty in every terrain type and height for these troops.

Name: Night Vision
Description: Hunter of the night. These troops suffer no vision loss at night at all.

Name: Pain Weakness
Description: These troops are completely unfit for any direct battle! Any injury causes them to fight less effectively.

Name: Cold Exposure
Description: The lack of coverage or the wrong type of clothing can kill anyone just like the enemy in a cold place. Warm up or be preserved forever.

Name: Heat Exposure
Description: The cloth or armour these troops are wearing is not suitable for the hot climate. The heat will render the body reaching a mortality state eventually.

Name: Cowardice
Description: Craven! Useless! These troops are comprised of cowards and their morale will decrease even more from any factors.

Name: Treachery
Description: Betrayal! These wretch troops are more likely to surrender and change side right away in dire situations. But, they will still try to flee instead if the enemy force will not accept surrender.

Name: Sadism
Description: These troops are addicted to inflicting pain and death. The more injury and death they inflict, the higher the morale.

Name: Masochism
Description: These troops are addicted to receiving pain and death. The more injury and death they suffer, the higher the morale.

Name: Loves Fear
Description: These troops actually love to feel fear. Being near anyone that causes or is affected by terror and fear, regardless of side, increase their morale.

Name: Seductive Charm
Description: These troops’ appearance can charm enemies, making them distracted and less effective in combat.

Name: Disgusting Taste
Description: The worst taste of meat ever exist. No one will ever want to devour these creatures, even if they have no taste buds.

Name: Rusty And Dirty
Description: These troops’ weapons are covered with nasty rust making them less effective overall. However, their attacks can cause infection to injured enemies, making them recover slower and harder to heal.

Name: Thrist For Blood
Description: These troops thirst for blood, literally! The longer they fight, the better their morale. They also suffer an increasing morale penalty the longer they stay out of combat.

Name: Tainted Blood
Description: Tainted blood is very dangerous if it comes into contact with any untainted creature. Hence, melee combat against enemies with tainted blood is extremely inadvisable.

Name: Acid Blood
Description: Bad news for everyone! Acid is raining down on whoever harm these creatures. Anyone that is affected by acid blood suffers combat penalty and also injury.

Name: Fantastic Beard
Description: These troops have an impressive beard that inspires all other dwarfs in the realm and battle.

Name: Hard Skull
Description: Primal protection for the most valuable part of one's body. These troops are more resistant to critical strikes to their head.

Name: Mountain Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in mountain terrain.

Name: Hill Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in hill terrain.

Name: Forest Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in forest terrain.

Name: Cloud Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in sky.

Name: Desert Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in desert terrain.

Name: Snow Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in snow terrain.

Name: Water Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in water terrain.

Name: Plain Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in plain terrain.

Name: Swamp Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in swamp terrain.

Name: Urban Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in urban terrain.

Name: Blight Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in blight terrain.

Name: Underground Hiding
Description: These troops can hide better in underground terrain.

Name: Night Stalking
Description: These troops can hide better at night.

Name: Ambush Expert
Description: These troops can hide in any terrain, nowhere is truly safe for the enemy.

Name: Battle Frenzy
Description: KILL! These berserkers can go into a frenzied state similar to orc wrath that is even crazier than normal berserk.

Name: Fear Magic
Description: It is natural to fear the unnatural. What can you do against something you can never truly understand?

Name: Scare Mount
Description: These troops can cause enemies' mount to panic or scare, which reduce enemy cavalries’ combat effectiveness and morale.

Name: Fearless Mount
Description: These troops’ mount cannot be panicked or broken and immune to Scare Mount.

Name: Human Killer
Description: Humans, they seem to be everywhere. So different, yet all so irritating. Time to make the world a better place by killing them all.

Name: Elf Murderer
Description: Those damn arrogant gaze! Those damn annoying sneers! Darn elves think they are above every other race, let's show those sharp ears the death they deserve!

Name: Dwarf Exterminator
Description: Short and stinky! What good do dwarves bring to the world anyway? Useless sods they all are.

Name: Orc Destroyer
Description: Orcs are nothing but a blight on civilisation. Their extinction will be another cornerstone of progress.

Name: Goblin Eradicator
Description: Nasty little things like these deserve to be eradicated. Kill them all and be rid of these pests for good, or they will come back even more.

Name: Halfling Annihilator
Description: Peace and love? Those who are not ready for war will never see peace.

Name: Animal Butcher
Description: Look at those valuable fangs and fur! Whoever deals the killing blow gets the prize!

Name: Lizardman Eraser
Description: Them scaly skins always are up to no good. We must erase them from the face of the earth so our children can live safely.

Name: Beastman Eliminator
Description: Higher than mere beast but lower than man. These creatures deserve no better! The hunt is on!

Name: Giant Terminator
Description: Big and brutish. Truly the greatest challenge for the greatest warrior.

Name: Dragon Slayer
Description: Some say dragons were the sole ruler of the world in the age of origin, the true symbol of power. Not for us, of course.

Name: Demon Banisher
Description: How dare those vile demons invade our world?! Go back to whatever the hell you all came from!

Name: Undead Liberator
Description: Nothing less than blasphemy, the existence of these undead creatures. It is our duty to free them of these miserable states they are in.

Name: Fairy Crusher
Description: Pure and innocence, is it? Those who say that obviously never meet the real one. It's always fun to crush annoying flies!

Name: Gremlin Bankrupter
Description: To be the slave to money is make money your biggest weak point. Just make them lose all the money and watch them kill themselves over that.

Name: Wizard Hunters
Description: "The unnatural of magecraft is too dangerous for any person to possess. Therefore, any person who practices the art of magic is punishable by death." The Absolute Law of Mortal Life, Fifth Act: Third Article.

Name: Vindictive
Description: Revenge is best served cold, is what they often say. Well, someone also likes to have it hot!

Name: Animal Instinct
Description: The fundamental of every animal is to survive. Based on that instinct, these creatures will flee much faster in a losing fight but will give it all when they cannot escape and are less likely to surrender.

Name: Phoenix Blood
Description: The blood of an immortal bird, while not making one immune to damage and disease, can help improve regenerative ability greatly and also allowing the body to resurrect with enough energy.

Name: Incorporeal
Description: "How can we kill this thing!?", An unknown soldier before being struck down. These troops cannot be damaged by normal weapons only from magic and magical weapon but also fight less effective.

Name: Oath Of The Eternal
Description: Bound by the Eternal Oath, these soldiers will fight on even in death.

Name: Light Vision Intolerance
Description: Blind by the light! These troops cannot withstand the sight of sunlight, making them unsuitable for daytime combat.

Name: Night Vision Intolerance
Description: These troops cannot see well in the night at all, which reduces their combat effectiveness greatly.

Name: Nocturnal
Description: These troops fight better at night but worse at day.

Name: Willbreaker
Description: Even the strongest will can be broken. These troops can make psychological resistance properties and abilities such as Strong Will of nearby enemies less effective.

Name: Adore Melody
Description: These troops love music dearly and will receive better combat bonuses from music. However, if the music stops, these troops will then receive a combat penalty.

Name: Loathe Melody
Description: These troops hate music and will receive combat penalties from music. If the music stops, these troops will receive a combat bonus after.

Name: Salted Phase
Description: The salted sea requires unconditional allegiance from those who wish to pass it. Only those with the strongest will can survive in this unforgiving above the true abyss.

Name: Sorrow Of Battle
Description: Woe for the world to see war and not peace. Our enemy too suffers the same fate as us.

Name: Smokey Wings At The Ground
Description: When these troops suffer a casualty, the Smokey Wings on the dead troops will drop to the ground. The smoke rising from the ground up will affect everyone without an anti-smokey mask.

Name: Anti-Smokey Mask
Description: These troops cannot be affected by Smokey ability.

Name: Strong Will
Description: To have strong will is much harder to achieve than having a strong body. Only a few are so well trained to face the unknown after all.

Name: Fullmoon Jubilance
Description: The fateful day! These troops will fight fiercely to the death to fulfil the prophecy.

Name: Halfmoon Preparation
Description: There is no glory yet in battle before the full moon. These troops will fight more reserved and more likely to retreat in a losing fight.

Name: Crescentmoon Sacrifice
Description: The rites must be made to hasten the arrival of the true moon! Sacrifices must be chosen!

Name: Darkmoon Melancholy
Description: The darkest day! It is forbidden to die on this day at all costs.

Name: Bloodmoon Coming
Description: The prophecy has been fulfilled! The gate of heaven is opened at last!

Name: Assassination
Description: These troops can stay hidden while attacking if no enemy can spot them.

Name: Sniping
Description: These troops can stay hidden while shooting.

Name: Invisible
Description: These troops can stay hidden until fighting in melee.

Name: Full Awareness
Description: These troops can detect enemies from any direction at all times.

Name: Partial Awareness
Description: These troops can detect enemies from any direction when not fighting.

Name: True Sight
Description: These troops can always detect any hidden enemy and trap.

Name: True Aims
Description: These troops will These troops will always hit the enemy regardless of range and bypass obstacle defence by half. The cowardly enemy cannot hide behind their shield anymore.always hit enemy regardless of range and bypass obstacle defense by half.The cowardly enemy cannot hide behind their shield anymore.

Name: Healing Aura
Description: These troops possess an aura that cause nearby friendly troops to be able to heal themselves.

Name: Regeneration
Description: These troops can heal themselves in time without needing a medical assistant.

Name: Fast Regeneration
Description: These troops can heal themselves even in battle as long as it is not attacked.

Name: Limb Regeneration
Description: These troops can regenerate their lost limbs, making them able to completely become combat-ready again after resting.

Name: Immortal
Description: These troops are immortal and cannot be killed by any means. Not even magic can harm them.

Name: Gunpowder Weapon
Description: These troops carry a weapon that requires gunpowder to operate. The wet or water-related status will reduce the weapon's performance.
